  "statement": "# Valid Parenthesis String\n\nReturn whether `*` can be treated as `(`, `)`, or empty to make the parenthesis string valid.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: s = (*)\nOutput: true\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: s = (*))\nOutput: true\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: s = )*(\nOutput: false\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Track the local choice that leaves the most room for future choices, or sort intervals so conflicts can be resolved with one pass.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def checkValidString(self, s):\n        low = high = 0\n        for ch in s:\n            if ch == '(':\n                low += 1; high += 1\n            elif ch == ')':\n                low -= 1; high -= 1\n            else:\n                low -= 1; high += 1\n            if high < 0: return False\n            low = max(low, 0)\n        return low == 0\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Sort first when relative order drives the decision.",
    "Keep the smallest state that proves future feasibility."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def checkValidString(self, s):\n        pass\n"
  },
